bomasnow appears to be based on a cross between an {{wp|Evergreen|evergreen tree}} covered in {{wp|snow}} and a {{wp|yeti}}. It may also be based on 樹氷 \'\'juhyou\'\', trees completely covered in snow known as "snow monsters".\n\n====Name origin====\nAbomasnow is a shortening of the term \'\'Abominable Snowman\'\', another name for the {{wp|yeti}}.\n\nYukinooh may come to mean 雪の王 \'\'yuki no ō\'\' (snow king).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Grass|type2=Ice\n|ja=ユキノオー \'\'Yukinooh\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|雪の王 \'\'yuki no ō\'\'|snow king}}\n|de=Rexblisar|demeaning=From \'\'Rex\'\' and \'\'blizzard\'\'\n|fr=Blizzaroi|frmeaning=From \'\'blizzard\'\' and \'\'{{tt|roi|king}}\'\'\n|es=Abomasnow|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Abomasnow|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=눈설왕 \'\'Nunseolwang\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|눈 \'\'nun\'\'|snow}}, {{tt|설 (雪) \'\'seol\'\'|snow}}, and {{tt|왕 (王) \'\'wang\'\'|king}}\n|zh_yue=暴雪王 \'\'Bouhsyutwohng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Same as Mandarin name\n|zh_cmn=暴雪王 \'\'Bàoxuěwáng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|暴風雪 \'\'bào\u200bfēng\u200bxuě\'\'|blizzard}} and {{tt|王 \'\'wáng\'\'|king}}. Literally "Violent snow king"\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Notes==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{Smash Bros.}}<br>\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Grass|type2=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Grass|prevnum=459|prev=Snover|nextnum=461|next=Weavile}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Rexblisar]]\n[[es:Abomasnow]]\n[[fr:Blizzaroi]]\n[[it:Abomasnow]]\n[[ja:ユキノオー]]\n[[zh:暴雪王]]'}